message.content: cs.SD, cs.SD is the most likely category as it stands for Sound and Music Computing, which is directly related to the topic of the paper. Other likely categories could be cs.LG (Machine Learning) as deep learning is a subfield of machine learning, cs.CV (Computer Vision) as convolutional neural networks are commonly used in image processing and can be applied to spectrograms, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as the paper discusses audio retrieval and similarity retrieval, and cs.CL (Computation and Language) as recurrent neural networks are commonly used in natural language processing and can be applied to audio event detection.
